5) In March 2025, USCIS issued a Federal Register notice for termination of parole for Cubans, Haitians, Nicaragua, and Venezuelans. As part of this termination process, USCIS issued notices to aliens with an approved Employment Authorization Document (EAD) based on their parole (category (c)(11)). This action reverted previously approved (c)(11) EADs to a pending status. In April 2025, a stay was issued (Svitlana Doe, et al., v. Noem, et. al., No. 25-cv-10495 (D. Mass. Apr. 14, 2025)), which temporarily halted the implementation of those actions. As a result, the pending (c)(11) EADs were reverted to an approved status.
